OL,3,CCumbrian MP first to speak out against
OL,4,Cgovernment changes to inheritance tax
OL,6,FIntervening, Reform UK deputy leader
OL,7,FRichard Tice asked: "Will the minister
OL,8,Fagree, given the massive discrepancy
OL,9,Fin the impact of this policy, that if
OL,10,Fthe data shows in 12 months, in 24
OL,11,Fmonths that the Government had got
OL,12,Fthis catastrophically wrong, that you
OL,13,Fwill actually revisit this policy and
OL,14,Fdo a U-turn?"
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                G16/17
